# BCH Basic: Structural Baker-Campbell-Hausdorff theorem

The BCH element `bch a b = logOnePlus(exp(a) ┬╖ exp(b) - 1)` is the unique element Z
satisfying `exp(Z) = exp(a) ┬╖ exp(b)`, defined for тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ < ln 2.

## Main definitions

* `bch a b`: the BCH element, defined via the log series applied to `exp(a) ┬╖ exp(b) - 1`

## Main results

* `exp_bch`: `exp(bch a b) = exp a * exp b` for тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ < ln 2
* `logOnePlus_exp_sub_one`: `logOnePlus(exp a - 1) = a` for тАЦaтАЦ < ln 2  (log тИШ exp = id)
* `norm_bch_sub_add_le`: `тАЦbch a b - (a + b)тАЦ тЙд C ┬╖ (тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ)┬▓ ┬╖ exp(тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ)`

## References

* [Baker, H.F., *Proc. London Math. Soc.*, 1905]
* [Campbell, J.E., *Proc. London Math. Soc.*, 1897]
* [Hausdorff, F., *Ber. Verhandl. S├дchs. Akad. Wiss. Leipzig*, 1906]
-/

