contains the per-group precursors; the full `bch_quintic_term` bound combines
all 4 groups via triangle inequality with the appropriate `(720)тБ╗┬╣`-scalar
factors.

Each group's diff telescopes per-word: a word `w(z, y)` with k z-positions has
diff `w(z, y) тИТ w(x, y) = ╬гт▒╝ [product]┬╖(zтИТx)┬╖[product]`, with k summands.
Each summand has 4 letters from `{x, z, y}` (each тЙд M) and one (zтИТx) factor
(of norm `тАЦz тИТ xтАЦ`), giving a per-summand bound of `MтБ┤ ┬╖ тАЦz тИТ xтАЦ`. -/

