/-- **Norm bound for `bch_septic_term`**: `тАЦZтВЗ(a, b)тАЦ тЙд (тАЦaтАЦ+тАЦbтАЦ)тБ╖`.

The actual ╬г|coef|/30240 = 2976/30240 = 31/315 тЙИ 0.098413 (tight).
The proof uses a uniform per-i bound `216/30240` (max |scaled coef|),
giving `╬г тЙд 126┬╖216/30240 = 27216/30240 = 9/10 тЙд 1`. -/
theorem norm_bch_septic_term_le (a b : ЁЭФ╕) :
    тАЦbch_septic_term ЁЭХВ a bтАЦ тЙд (тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ) ^ 7 := by
  set s := тАЦaтАЦ + тАЦbтАЦ with hs_def
  have hs_nn : 0 тЙд s := by positivity
  have ha_le : тАЦaтАЦ тЙд s := by linarith [norm_nonneg b]
  have hb_le : тАЦbтАЦ тЙд s := by linarith [norm_nonneg a]
  have hs7_nn : 0 тЙд s ^ 7 := pow_nonneg hs_nn 7
  rw [bch_septic_term_eq_sum]
  calc тАЦтИС i : Fin 126, bchSepticTerm (ЁЭХВ := ЁЭХВ) a b iтАЦ
      тЙд тИС i : Fin 126, тАЦbchSepticTerm (ЁЭХВ := ЁЭХВ) a b iтАЦ := norm_sum_le _ _
    _ тЙд тИС _i : Fin 126, (216 / 30240 : тДЭ) * s^7 :=
        Finset.sum_le_sum (fun i _ => bchSepticTerm_norm_le (ЁЭХВ := ЁЭХВ) a b s ha_le hb_le hs_nn i)
    _ = 126 * ((216 / 30240 : тДЭ) * s^7) := by
        rw [Finset.sum_const, Finset.card_univ, Fintype.card_fin]; ring
    _ тЙд 1 * s^7 := by nlinarith [hs7_nn]
    _ = s ^ 7 := one_mul _

/-! ## Vanishing of `bch_septic_term` on `(╬▒тАвV, ╬▓тАвV)`

Since `bch(╬▒тАвV, ╬▓тАвV) = log(exp(╬▒тАвV)┬╖exp(╬▓тАвV)) = (╬▒+╬▓)тАвV` for any
`╬▒, ╬▓ : ЁЭХВ` (all commutators `[V, V]` vanish), every ╧ДтБ╖ Taylor
coefficient of bch at pure-V inputs must vanish:

  `bch_septic_term ЁЭХВ (╬▒ тАв V) (╬▓ тАв V) = 0`.

Analog of `SymmetricQuintic.symmetric_bch_septic_poly_apply_smul_smul`
for the (non-palindromic) bch deg-7 coefficient. Foundation for the
future `octic_pure_identity` (deg-7 cancellation algebraic identity at
substituted polynomials, the deg-9 analog of `septic_pure_identity`). -/

