/-- **Ninth-order BCH: degree-8 cancellation identity (nonic_pure_identity)**

Analog of `octic_pure_identity` at one degree higher. After substituting
ea тЖТ exp(a), eb тЖТ exp(b), the deg-8 part of
  `┬╜W_H1 + тЕУy┬│ тИТ ┬╝yтБ┤ + тЕХyтБ╡ тИТ тЕЩyтБ╢ + тЕРyтБ╖ тИТ тЕЫyтБ╕ тИТ CтВГ тИТ CтВД тИТ CтВЕ тИТ CтВЖ тИТ CтВЗ тИТ CтВИ`
vanishes. This identity expresses that vanishing as an explicit pure {a, b}
ring identity, with the deg-8 leading term `bch_octic_term`.

Notation:
- `z = a + b`
- `T_k = y_dk` for k = 2..7 (deg-k of `y = exp(a)┬╖exp(b) тИТ 1`)
- `W8 = 2┬╖y_d8 тИТ (y┬▓)_d8`
- `y3_8 = (y┬│)_d8`, `y4_8 = (yтБ┤)_d8`, `y5_8 = (yтБ╡)_d8`,
  `y6_8 = (yтБ╢)_d8`, `y7_8 = (yтБ╖)_d8`, `(yтБ╕)_d8 = zтБ╕`

Foundation for stepping stone 1 (`symmetric_bch_septic_sub_poly_axiom`)
discharge тАФ the deg-9 analog of T2-F7e. -/
private theorem nonic_pure_identity (ЁЭХВ : Type*) [RCLike ЁЭХВ] {ЁЭФ╕ : Type*}
    [NormedRing ЁЭФ╕] [NormedAlgebra ЁЭХВ ЁЭФ╕] (a b : ЁЭФ╕) :
